President Obama has announced his intent to nominate William J. Hybl and Michael P. O'Rielly for key administration posts. William J. Hybl is nominated for a position on the United States Advisory Commission on Public Diplomacy. He currently serves as the Chairman and CEO of the El Pomar Foundation, Chairman of Garden City Company, and Vice Chairman of Broadmoor Hotel, Inc. He has been Chairman of the Advisory Commission since 2008 and has been a member since 1990. Hybl has also served as a Civilian Aide to the Secretary of the Army for Colorado and was a U.S. Representative to the United Nations General Assembly in 2001-2002. He was also the President of the United States Olympic Committee from 1991 to 1992 and from 1996 to 2000. Michael P. O'Rielly is nominated for the position of Commissioner at the Federal Communications Commission. He has been serving as a Commissioner since November 2013. Prior to that, he held various positions in the offices of U.S. Senators John Cornyn and Jon Kyl. He has also worked in the United States Senate and House of Representatives, focusing on banking, technology, transportation, trade, and commerce. O'Rielly received his B.A. from the University of Rochester.